Subject: [PATCH 57/57] web-app: voice-message waveform, remembered playback
 position (experimental)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Builds on the A1 custom controls, still gated behind experimentalAudioPlayerControls
(off → playback renders exactly as before). Two additions plus a recorder-meter
upgrade, all progressive: the waveform never gates playback and silently keeps
the plain A1 seek bar on any failure.

Waveform (progressive enhancement over the A1 range bar):
- new peaks.ts pipeline getPeaks(src): in-session bounded Map cache (~100, FIFO,
  no persistent cache — measure first, issue A2.5) → fetch → arrayBuffer →
  decodeAudioData → hand channel-0 to a shared worker for max-abs bucketing
  (N=64). Bounded ~4s budget via Promise.race + AbortController on the fetch;
  any error/timeout resolves null (log.debug at most) and the player falls back.
- decode stays on the main thread on purpose: decodeAudioData only exists on
  Audio/OfflineAudioContext, which a plain (non-AudioWorklet) Worker can't
  construct, so a worker can't decode — only the cheap bucketing loop is
  offloaded. Worker is lazily created once and shared; if construction throws
  (upstream builds without the web-app shell don't serve the file) it resolves
  null forever, i.e. the fallback path.
- Waveform.tsx renders a canvas UNDER the range (range stays THE interactive
  seek control — drag guard, keyboard, aria intact); when peaks land the range
  goes fully transparent (track + thumb) and the canvas draws 64 bars, played
  portion in --colorPrimary, unplayed in currentColor at 35%. Redraws off the
  existing currentTime/duration state (no extra listeners), handles dpr. No
  ResizeObserver — draws use live clientWidth and are driven by playback state.

Performance tracking from day one (on-device only): peaks.ts emits User Timing
measures sc:waveform:{fetch,decode,bucket} with detail {durationSec, bytes} and,
on fallback, a sc:waveform:fallback mark with {reason}; all wrapped in try/catch.
The web-app Diagnostics panel gains a "Waveform (ms)" section reading them back
(count/last/avg/min/max per stage + last file + fallback count), omitted when
nothing has run.

Remembered position (positionStore.ts): localStorage JSON map keyed by src
(stable per message file; avoids threading messageId), value {t, at}, capped
~300 with oldest-by-at pruning, all storage access try/caught. On loadedmetadata
restore a saved t in (1, duration-1); save throttled ~2s while playing and
immediately on pause; clear on natural end.

Seek carryover to the singleton (the A1 ponytail limitation, now fixed — comment
removed): (a) the mutex onPlay carries a restored/scrubbed local currentTime onto
the singleton when the src actually changed (it otherwise always starts a fresh
src at 0); (b) the AudioPlayer mirror pushes a held local position onto the
singleton when the singleton just started this src from the top (auto-advance to
a half-heard message) — one-way only, a remounting local element must never yank
back a mid-play singleton.

Recorder meter: when the setting is on, the segmented VolumeMeter is replaced by
a rolling live waveform drawn with the SAME canvas routine as the player
(exported drawBars, not duplicated) over a bounded history of recent RMS levels;
setting off leaves the VolumeMeter untouched.

Tests: node:test for computePeaks (empty/constant/spike-localization) and mocha
for positionStore cap/prune/clear via an injectable storage + clock shim.

Review hardening (adversarial pass over this commit):
- Worker URL is now resolved relative to the document (new URL('waveform-worker.js',
  location.href), the web-app's BASE convention) instead of a root-absolute path, so
  it loads on subpath deploys (e.g. GitHub Pages project sites) rather than 404ing.
- A worker load error (async, doesn't throw at construction) now flips to a
  permanent fallback: worker is dropped and in-flight callers settle to null at
  once — no 4s hang, no leaked AudioBuffers, no unbounded pending map. computePeaks
  short-circuits once the worker is known dead, and User Timing no longer records
  phantom successes on aborted/worker-died runs. getPeaks caches the in-flight
  promise so concurrent bubbles for the same src share one pipeline.
- Position lifecycle vs the mutex takeover: restore never yanks back a singleton
  mid-playing this src; the takeover cleanup saves the exact position before
  zeroing; replay-from-top re-applies the saved position; clear-on-ended moved to
  the singleton so it fires across unmount. positionStore.read() rejects
  valid-but-wrong-typed JSON instead of throwing on every accessor.
- Recorder meter resets its history per recording and draws imperatively from the
  per-buffer volume callback, so digital silence (identical RMS) no longer freezes
  the waveform via React's state bailout.
- No layout jump: the seek row reserves the waveform's height from first paint, and
  the live waveform shares the meter's footprint (incl. the <400px hide rule).
